Exercise 2.17 Write as a single power by expressing each number as a prime power.


a) \(\displaystyle 8 \times 343\)


b) \(\displaystyle 16 \times 81\)


c) \(\displaystyle 25 \times 49\)


d) \(\displaystyle 25 \times 49\)


e) \(\displaystyle 9 \times 25\)


f) \(\displaystyle 8 \times 343\)








TipūüĒć View Solutions





a)
\[
\begin{aligned}
8\times 343=2^{3}\times 7^{3}=(2\times 7)^{3}=14^{3}=2744
\end{aligned}
\]
b)
\[
\begin{aligned}
16\times 81=2^{4}\times 3^{4}=(2\times 3)^{4}=6^{4}=1296
\end{aligned}
\]
c)
\[
\begin{aligned}
25\times 49=5^{2}\times 7^{2}=(5\times 7)^{2}=35^{2}=1225
\end{aligned}
\]
d)
\[
\begin{aligned}
25\times 49=5^{2}\times 7^{2}=(5\times 7)^{2}=35^{2}=1225
\end{aligned}
\]
e)
\[
\begin{aligned}
9\times 25=3^{2}\times 5^{2}=(3\times 5)^{2}=15^{2}=225
\end{aligned}
\]
f)
\[
\begin{aligned}
8\times 343=2^{3}\times 7^{3}=(2\times 7)^{3}=14^{3}=2744
\end{aligned}
\]





